article.headline: Towson 79, Cincinnati Christian 40
article.story: RICHMOND, Ky. -- Mike Burwell scored 18 points, leading four Towson State players in double figures, and the Tigers never trailed in beating Cincinnati Christian 79-40 on Monday. The game was Towson's final game in the Comfort Suites Invitational at Eastern Kentucky. The Tigers went 3-1 in the tournament and are 3-2 this season. Marcus Damas scored 12 points for Towson State, while Kris Walden and Bilal Dixon scored 10 apiece. Dixon also had a game-high 11 rebounds as the Tigers owned a 46-22 advantage on the boards. Towson led 39-19 at the half and by as many as 42 in the final minutes. DJ McCommons had nine points to lead the Eagles (1-4). Cincinnati Christian plays in NAIA.
